 thrv_text_element"><h2 class=3D"">What is Effective Field Goal Percentage?=
</h2><p>One of the most important new statistics is <strong>effective field=
 goal percentage</strong>.</p><p>It was first introduced in 2002 by <a href=
=3D"https://twitter.com/deano_lytics" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"tve-froala=
 fr-basic" style=3D"outline: none;" rel=3D"noopener">Dean Oliver</a> in his=
 book, <a href=3D"https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/420949.Basketball_on_=
Paper" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"tve-froala fr-basic" style=3D"outline: no=
ne;" rel=3D"noopener">"Basketball on Paper"</a></p><p><em>(Which is one of =
the <a href=3D"https://www.basketballforcoaches.com/basketball-books/" targ=
et=3D"_blank" class=3D"tve-froala" style=3D"outline: none;">100 books we re=
commend all coaches read before they die</a>)</em></p><p>Dean recognized th=
e shortcomings of field goal percentage and proposed Effective Field Goal p=
ercentage (eFG%) -- one of his =E2=80=9Cfour factors=E2=80=9D to predict a =
team=E2=80=99s success.</p><p>It's a simple calculation that weighs the add=
ed benefit that a made three pointer has, allowing for more accurate evalua=
tion of both teams and individual players.</p><p>This had made some =E2=80=
=9Ctraditional=E2=80=9D statistics like field goal percentage somewhat anti=
quated.</p></div><div class=3D"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element"><h3 class=3D=
"">Why Is It Important?</h3><p>Regular field goal percentage, much like bat=
ting average in baseball, doesn=E2=80=99t do a great job of fully explainin=
g a player=E2=80=99s offensive contribution.</p><p>Effective field goal per=
centage does a better job because it:</p><ul class=3D""><li class=3D"">Prop=
erly weighs the value of a three pointer compared to a made two point baske=
t.</li><li class=3D"">Is a better indicator for previous and future offensi=
ve performance.</li><li class=3D"">Removes the bias of a higher overall fie=
ld goal percentage.</li></ul></div><div class=3D"thrv_responsive_video thrv=
_wrapper tcb-lazy-load tcb-lazy-load-youtube" data-type=3D"youtube" data-re=
