</div><div class=3D"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element"><h2 class=3D"">Calculat=
ing Effective Field Goal Percentage</h2><p>Effective field goal percentage =
is the most heavily weighted of the <a href=3D"https://squared2020.com/2017=
/09/05/introduction-to-olivers-four-factors/" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"tv=
e-froala fr-basic" style=3D"outline: none;" rel=3D"noopener">Four Factors</=
a> at 40%.</p><p><em>(The other three factors are: offensive rebounding per=
centage, turnover percentage, and free throw rate.)</em></p><p><strong>To c=
alculate effective field goal percentage:</strong></p><ul class=3D""><li cl=
ass=3D"">Assign 1 point for every made two-point basket</li><li class=3D"">=
Assign 1.5 points for every three-point basket</li><li class=3D"">Add the t=
wo numbers together</li><li class=3D"">Divide by the total number of field =
goals attempted</li><li class=3D"">Multiply by 100 to get a percentage</li>=
</ul><p>An example:</p><p>Say a player shoots 5 - 10 in a game from the fie=
ld, including 3 - 4 from behind the 3-point line.</p><p>That would be:</p><=
ul class=3D""><li class=3D"">2 two-point baskets (2 points)</li><li class=
=3D"">3 three-point baskets (4.5 points)</li><li class=3D"">6.5 points tota=
l (2 + 4.5)</li><li class=3D"">6.5/10 =3D 0.65</li><li class=3D"">0.65 * 10=
0% =3D <strong>65 eFG%</strong></li></ul></div><div class=3D"thrv_wrapper t=
hrv_text_element"><h2 class=3D"">Field Goal Percentage (FG%) vs. Effective =
Field Goal Percentage (eFG%)</h2><p>Let=E2=80=99s look at two different pla=
yers shooting percentages and try to evaluate their shooting.</p><p>Both pl=
ay the (3) and would be considered the =E2=80=9Cgo-to guy=E2=80=9D on the o=
ffensive end.</p><ul class=3D""><li class=3D"">Player A Field Goal Percenta=
ge - 45.3%</li><li class=3D"">Player B Field Goal Percentage - 50.4%</li></=
ul><p>By this number it should be obvious who the better shooter is...</p><=
p>Putting aside factors like usage rate, it seems Player B is the better of=
fensive player, right?</p><p>But let=E2=80=99s look at their eFG%...</p><ul=
 class=3D""><li class=3D"">Player A eFG%: 52.6%</li><li class=3D"">Player B=
 eFG%: 52.1%</li></ul><p><strong>Player A is Celtics superstar Jayson Tatum=
.</strong></p><p><strong>Player B is the midrange master DeMar DeRozan of t=
he Chicago Bulls.</strong></p><p>DeMar Derozan makes his living between the=
 paint and three point line. But while he=E2=80=99s an excellent midrange s=
hooter, his shot profile requires him to make those shots at a very high ra=
te to maintain efficiency.</p><p>But for Jayson Tatum, not only is he a sol=
id three-point shooter (shot 35% on his threes), but he takes a huge number=
 of them (8.6 threes a game this season).</p><p>Compare that to DeRozan who=
 also made 35% of his threes, but took just two per game.</p><p>Tatum=E2=80=
=99s shots carry more =E2=80=9Cvalue,=E2=80=9D allowing him to make up for =
his lower field goal percentage because the shots he makes are worth more.<=
/p></div><div class=3D"thrv_wrapper thrv_text_element"><h2 class=3D"">What=
=E2=80=99s a Good eFG%?</h2><p>Most players shoot between 40% and 50% from =
the field.</p><p>For the most part, we accept anything above that as "excel=
lent" and anything below that is considered "poor" shooting.</p><p>Effectiv=
e field goal percentage hasn=E2=80=99t received the same treatment, even as=
 teams start to rely on it more to evaluate performance.</p><p>The statisti=
c isn=E2=80=99t always readily available, although websites like <a href=3D=
"http://teamrankings.com/" target=3D"_blank" class=3D"tve-froala fr-basic" =
style=3D"outline: none;" rel=3D"noopener">teamrankings.com</a> are a great =
resource for =E2=80=9Cadvanced=E2=80=9D stats.</p><p>For many NBA evaluator=
s, an eFG% of 51% or higher is decent, while anything below 50% is subpar.<=
/p><p>Julius Randle, for example, was last among NBA qualifiers last year i=
n effective field goal percentage at 45.9%.</p><p>Here=E2=80=99s the top-25=
 players in the NBA in 2021-2022 in effective field goal percentage:</p></d=
iv><div class=3D"thrv_wrapper tve_image_caption" data-css=3D"tve-u-18183b2f=
